{"type":"step-attempt","step":"design","sessionId":"258fb23e-9f8e-40b8-85da-5a6cf78b8a84","outcome":{"verdict":"success","findingsPath":null,"error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"reason":"Wrote design.md, spec.md, tasks.md under specrunner/changes/approved-not-overturned-by-fixer-budget/ on branch change/approved-not-overturned-by-fixer-budget-d294f4e0.\n\nRoot cause traced: the fixer entry exhaustion check (pipeline.ts:493-499 via tryExhaust at :563) ignores the preceding reviewer verdict. When a reviewer returns approved with fixable findings, findings-routing sends it to code-fixer; if the paired fixer budget is exhausted, it escalates with \"code-review did not approve after N iterations\" despite an approval.\n\nPlan (engine-scoped, no transition-table row deletion, no verdict-rule change):\n- T-01: add pure helper lastReviewerFixableCount to reviewer-chain.ts.\n- T-02: add DomainEvent pipeline:fixer:budget-skipped (kernel + core/event) + PipelineLogger subscription.\n- T-03: in runInternal, right after transition resolution (before episode-reset/exhaustion checks), when outcome===approved AND nextStep is a fixer AND getFixerIter(fixer) >= effectiveMax, re-route to the reviewer's clean approved target (found via the non-fixer approved row). This folds \"approved+fixable but budget-exhausted\" into the existing \"approved with no fixable\" clean pass-through, so downstream bookkeeping is identical for both standard (buildReviewerChainTransitions) and parallel (buildParallelReviewerTransitions) paths without touching either builder. handleExhausted is NOT called, so the approved verdict/findings are preserved.\n- T-04: record omission in history (warning: step name + omitted count + fixer + target) and emit the event.\n- T-05: tests T1 (standard, with break-verification), T2 (parallel, independent), T3 (omission recorded), T4 (needs-fix exhaustion unchanged), T5 (findings retained), plus requirement-5 assertion (no \"did not approve\" on approved).\n- T-06: backward-compat; confirmed no existing test asserts the buggy approved-exhaustion path (TC-061/062 use needs-fix or no-fixable approved), typecheck && test green.\n\nRequirement 5 is satisfied as a consequence of requirement 1 (no message edit needed; LOOP_ERROR_CODES unchanged).","status":"success"},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-19T05:57:41.803Z","endedAt":"2026-07-19T06:10:09.114Z","commitOid":"437c0c5c8e2267021ecbf9ebd1933edfc8674976"}
